shon  .","English (London): variant of   Marchant  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Marchant was born in 1485, in Rotherfield, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mary Coomber. He died about 1531, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1485–Abt 1531":"1485–umbes 1531","1485–1531":"1485–1531","1523–1588":"1523–1588","1523":"1523","1588":"1588","Abt 1531":"umbes 1531","1531":"1531","1485":"1485","abt 1531":"umbes 1531","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Saintbury, , Gloucestershire, England":"Saintbury, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rotherfield, Sussex, England":"Rotherfield, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–Abt 1531":"1485–noin 1531","1485–1531":"1485–1531","1523–1588":"1523–1588","1523":"1523","1588":"1588","Abt 1531":"noin 1531","1531":"1531","1485":"1485","abt 1531":"noin 1531","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Saintbury, , Gloucestershire, England":"Saintbury, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rotherfield, Sussex, England":"Rotherfield, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1485–Abt 1531":"1485–environ 1531","1485–1531":"1485–1531","1523–1588":"1523–1588","1523":"1523","1588":"1588","Abt 1531":"environ 1531","1531":"1531","1485":"1485","abt 1531":"environ 1531","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Saintbury, , Gloucestershire, England":"Saintbury, Gloucestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Rotherfield, Sussex, England":"Roth